Subject: [PATCH] P3: Decompose large components and services (database types +
 workout helpers)
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

### Motivation
- Reduce architectural debt by starting a safe, incremental decomposition of large "god" files without changing visible behavior or tests.
- Separate UI helpers from container/orchestration logic in `WorkoutDashboard` and reduce conceptual coupling between `database.ts` and `trainingReadModels.ts` by moving domain types to a shared module.
- Create operational artifacts to document the decomposition plan, import map, risks and evidence for traceability and next phases.

### Description
- Extracted domain types into `src/services/database/database.types.ts` and re-exported them from `src/services/database.ts` to preserve existing imports/compatibility.
- Updated `src/services/trainingReadModels.ts` to import only the pure types from `database.database.types` to break the conceptual cycle with `database.ts`.
- Extracted pure helper logic from `src/components/WorkoutDashboard.tsx` into `src/components/workout-dashboard/workoutDashboard.helpers.ts` and updated the component to import those helpers.
- Added operational documentation under `.ops/p3-architecture-decomposition/` (`decomposition-plan.md`, `evidence.md`, `import-map.md`, `risk-register.md`) to record scope, decisions and next actions while keeping `DatabaseService` façade unchanged.

### Testing
- Ran `git diff --check` and `npm run lint` with no blocking issues reported.
- Ran `npm run typecheck` and TypeScript reported no errors after the refactor.
- Ran the test suite with `npm test` and observed all tests pass (`140` test files, `534` tests passed).
- Built the app with `npm run build` and the production build completed successfully.
